<br>
- Knowing that I have enough damage in my arsenal to kill myself in one shot. Now that's power!<br>
<br>
- Being rez friendly. I can get clerics to the zone I died in faster than any other class and get them out when they are done while never leaving my group.<br>
<br>
- Being able to decess that exp sponge in my group to IZ without them being able to say anything about it. /disband expsponge_01 /ooc LF player<br>
<br>
- Going back to zones that were difficult 10-15 levels ago and owning the zone by myself.<br>
<br>
- No one gets pissed when I go afk in a group, half the time they don't even know.<br>
<br>
- Being the train killer in noob zones.<br>
<br>
Seriously though, the crits are probably the most fun aspect. For soooo long no one really knew how much damage we were doing. The day they turned them on was the day wizards earned a lot more respect as a class.<br>
<br>
Also the Ice Comet spell effect. (Though I can't stand it personally) It alone drops a lot of jaws.<br>
